cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the security of machine learning systems, specifically support vector machines, in adversarial environments. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). However, given that the paper focuses on the empirical evaluation of SVMs and their susceptibility to attacks, cs.LG and cs.CR are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the impact of attacks on SVMs in real-world security problems, which further supports the inclusion of cs.AI and cs.CV as likely categories. Finally, the use of open-source code and datasets suggests that cs.DS could also be a relevant category.
